    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-24T17:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-24T17:40:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839L00/1623.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-24T18:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Article 86, Constitution, and Articles 27 and 36 of Báez electoral law prescribe
                    absolute majority, that is, 317 electors. Jiménez has secured 337. Article 34 of
                    Constitution in regard to congressional <pb facs="0373" n="257" xml:id="pg_257"
                    /> power of proclaiming elections should be complied with November 30th if
                    expected quorum meets. Jiménez regarded as next President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
